column5: Hi all,  Have a single trailor with steel down the middle. I think it would be alot easier if I had that Plastic track material that most sled trailors have.  Any idea where i can get a strip of it ? ANywhere in the GTA would be good. im in richmond hill.
Just find someone that needs to get rid of an old track, I've seen countless people use this instead of the store bought versions.
Carbide ski plastic drive on guides?? Saw it in Princess auto flyer for around $70... or Royal Distributing would have it I'm sure.
thanks guys,  GTA guys if someone has an old track taking up space PM me and ill come take it off your hands!
Check out:  www.superclamp.net  They are up the road from you in Barrie.
Royal distributing has everything your looking for , innisfil or guelph.
